RT @NYDailyNews: More than 100,000 New Yorkers woke up Christmas morning without electricity after a powerful storm lashed the Northeast overnight.

Westchester, Rockland, Ulster, Orange and Dutchess Counties were particularly hard hit, with 73,926 outages reported.
https://t.co/RDhj3TYv5v

text:
RT @NYDailyNews: A homeless man was cuffed for bashing a Gov. Cuomo staffer in the back of the head with a brick in a random Christmas Eve attack in Midtown.

He clobbered Lisa Cavanaugh in the back of her head with the brick in an apparently unprovoked attack, cops said.
https://t.co/tvYpEs2JEi

name: NYDailyNews
text:
A beloved Long Island church burned down on Christmas. 

It took 125 firefighters to battle the blaze at the Good Shepherd Lutheran Church in Levittown. 

The building was empty at the time of the fire.
